-- ING increases number of shares on offer in insurance arm sale
-- 
-- Tue Jul 01, 2014 01:03PM EDT
-- None



July 1 (Reuters) - Dutch financial services company ING Group NV <ING.AS> on Tuesday said it had increased by 10 percent to 77 million the number of ordinary shares it will list in its insurance arm, NN Group <NN_w.AS> due to "significant" investor demand.

The shares are due to begin trading on Wednesday in Amsterdam in one of the largest initial public offerings in Europe this year.